Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deriveTimingBudget(25.10)                            deriveTimingBudget(25.10)

Name
       deriveTimingBudget - Generates timing budgets for partitions for stand-
       alone implementation

Syntax
       deriveTimingBudget

       [-help]

       [-parameterized]

       [-cycleRatio | -stageBased]

       [-allIlmHinsts | -inst <instanceName >| -ptn <partitionName>]

       [-verbose]

       [-views <string>]

       Generates  timing budgets for partitions for standalone implementation.
       This command can also generate timing budgets on an instance basis  in-
       stead of partitions. The generated timing constraint files allow you to
       do  standalone block implementation. In case of partition based budget-
       ing, it also generates timing models that will allow you to  do  stand-
       alone top level implementation. This command also directs summary files
       into the default budget justification directory.

       Note: You must free the timing graph to use multiple deriveTimingBudget
       commands with different options.

       Innovus  operates in multi-mode multi-corner (MMMC) mode, and generates
       viewFilesautomatically for partition implementation and top-level  chip
       assembly.  Note that the deriveTimingBudget command does not generate a
       timing graph, if it already exists. Additionally,  user  will  have  to
       provide  a  timing graph generated without using deriveTimingBudget and
       must set the value of the setBudgetingMode -virtualOptEngine  parameter
       same as that of the command used to generate the timing graph.

       When  the  deriveTimingBudget command is run, all the public setBudget-
       ingMode parameters with their non-default values are  displayed  before
       the  intended  output of the deriveTimingBudget command, in an informa-
       tion message. This information message follows the format shown below:

       This command "deriveTimingBudget" required an extra checkout of license
       invs_hier. Additional license(s) checked out: 1 'Innovus_Hier_Opt'  li-
       cense(s)

       **INFO: User settings:

       setBudgetingMode -abutted true

       setBudgetingMode -fixTopLevelPaths all

       setBudgetingMode -masterClone merged

       setBudgetingMode -noHoldView true

Parameters
       ________________________________________________________

       | -help           |  Outputs a brief description that   |

       |                 |   includes the type and default     |

       |                 |   information for each              |

       |                 |   deriveTimingBudget parameter. For |

       |                 |   a detailed description of the     |

       |                 |   command and all its parameters,   |

       |                 |   use the man command:man           |

       |                 |   deriveTimingBudget                |

       |____________________________________|__________________|

       | -allIlmHinsts   |  Derives timing budgets only for    |

       |                 |   all the ILM-based partitions.     |

       |                 |   When this parameter is used,      |

       |                 |  the software automatically derives |

       |                 |   the list of ILM instances and     |

       |                 |   budgets for them.Note: The        |

       |                 |   -allIlmHinsts parameter           |

       |                 |   internally calls -inst based      |

       |                 |   budgeting. So, saving budgets     |

       |                 |  is only supported through the      |

       |                 |   saveTimingBudget command.         |

       |                 |   Therefore, it is necessary to run |

       |                 |   saveTimingBudget after            |

       |                 |   deriveTimingBudget                |

       |                 |   -allIlmHinsts,  else              |

       |                 |   savePartition will not save the   |

       |                 |   budgeting information of ILM      |

       |                 |   instances.                        |

       |____________________________________|__________________|

       | -cycleRatio     |  Honors the setCycleBudgetRatio     |

       |                 |   constraints and enables usage     |

       |                 |  of clock cycle time based          |

       |                 |   budgeting. If no                  |

       |                 |   setCycleBudgetRatio constraints   |

       |                 |   are applied:The top and block     |

       |                 |   default ratio is 20% and 80% of   |

       |                 |   the clock respectively.The        |

       |                 |   partition for start and end       |

       |                 |   points splits the block ratio     |

       |                 |  in 50% each.Equivalent default     |

       |                 |   constraint is as                  |

       |                 |   follows:setCycleBudgetRatio       |

       |                 |   -fromPtn {* .4} -toPtn {*         |

       |                 |   .4}setCycleBudgetRatio -fromPtn   |

       |                 |   {* .8}                            |

       |                 |  -toTopsetCycleBudgetRatio -fromTop |

       |                 |   -toPtn {* .8}Note: Do not use the |

       |                 |   setFixedBudget command with       |

       |                 |  this parameter.                    |

       |____________________________________|__________________|

       | -inst instanceName...                                   |

       |_______________________________________________________|

       |                 |  Performs budgeting for the         |

       |                 |   hierarchical instance(s). This    |

       |                 |   instance could be a black box.    |

       |                 |   You can derive timing budgets for |

       |                 |   black boxes and other instances   |

       |                 |   in the same run. Specify the      |

       |                 |   setBudgetingMode -mergeClones     |

       |                 |   parameter in addition to the      |

       |                 |   -inst parameter to obtain         |

       |                 |   worst-case budgets based on       |

       |                 |   worst-case data per-pin for       |

       |                 |   specified instances in a          |

       |                 |   master/clone set. If you          |

       |                 |  specify instances from more than   |

       |                 |   one master/clone set, the tool    |

       |                 |   derives separate worst-case       |

       |                 |   timing budgets for the            |

       |                 |  specified instances in each        |

       |                 |   set.Default: If you do not        |

       |                 |   specify this parameter, the       |

       |                 |   software derives budgets for      |

       |                 |  all the partitions.                |

       |____________________________________|__________________|

       | -parameterized  |  Generates constraints as a         |

       |                 |   function of the clock period.When |

       |                 |   you set this parameter, the       |

       |                 |   software generates timing         |

       |                 |   constraints, such as              |

       |                 |   set_input_delay and               |

       |                 |   set_output_delay constraints as a |

       |                 |   function of the clock period in   |

       |                 |   the top-level and block-level     |

       |                 |   SDCs.                             |

       |____________________________________|__________________|

       | -ptn partitionName                                    |

       |_______________________________________________________|

       |                 |  Performs budgeting for the         |

       |                 |   specified partition(s). Specify   |

       |                 |   the setBudgetingMode -mergeClones |

       |                 |   parameter in addition to the -ptn |

       |                 |   parameter to obtain worst-case    |

       |                 |   budgets based on worst-case       |

       |                 |  data per-pin for all partitions in |

       |                 |   the master/clone set containing   |

       |                 |   the partition.You cannot          |

       |                 |  specify -ptn if you use            |

       |                 |   -inst.Default: Performs budgeting |

       |                 |   on all partitions.                |

       |____________________________________|__________________|

       | -stageBased     |  Creates a quick stage-based        |

       |                 |   timing graph to be used for       |

       |                 |   timing budgeting. Timing          |

       |                 |   budgeting with the stage-based    |

       |                 |   timing graphs is used in very     |

       |                 |   early stages of the design,       |

       |                 |   before applying optimization      |

       |                 |  for quick budgets. This method     |

       |                 |  is more accurate than the          |

       |                 |   cycle-based timing budgeting.When |

       |                 |   this parameter is used, any       |

       |                 |   existing timing graph in the      |

       |                 |   design is overwritten by the      |

       |                 |   generated special quick           |

       |                 |   stage-based timing graph. The     |

       |                 |   following example presents the    |

       |                 |   scenarios in which this parameter |

       |                 |   can be used:reg2reg path          |

       |____________________________________|__________________|

       | -verbose        |   Enables        |                  |

       |                 |   various        |                  |

       |                 |   verbose        |                  |

       |                 |   controls.      |                  |

       |_________________|__________________|__________________|

       | -views string   |   Derives budget for multiple       |

       |                 |   views in parallel for reducing    |

       |                 |   the runtime.                      |

       |____________________________________|__________________|

Examples
              * For  MMMC  examples, see the "Timing Budgeting" chapter of the
                Innovus User Guide.

              * The following command creates a budget for the black box BBox:

                deriveTimingBudget -inst BBox

                saveTimingBudget -inst BBox

